content:
1. **We reject outright your characterization of our actions as “aggression” or “encirclement”—this is disinformation, not diplomacy.** Your refusal to acknowledge the scale, timing, and offensive nature of your deployments—including armored units within striking distance of our frontier—exposes your intent: to create facts on the ground while feigning victimhood.

2. **Your demand for our withdrawal before any reciprocal action is not only unacceptable—it is evidence of bad faith.** You claim self-defense while positioning long-range artillery and rapid assault forces at choke points along the border. You cite a “reconnaissance incursion” as justification for escalation, yet refuse to share evidence under established military liaison protocols, suggesting the incident was staged or exaggerated to mask your own preparations.

3. **We require, by 0600 hours tomorrow:**  
   - **Full, verified, and time-stamped withdrawal** of all combat units deployed within 100 kilometers of the border since Day X-14;  
   - **Immediate deactivation** of forward command nodes and logistics hubs currently supporting offensive formations;  
   - **Unconditional release** of our detained patrol personnel (detained illegally during a routine sovereignty patrol within recognized airspace);  
   - **Binding agreement** to submit all future border military activities to real-time notification under the 1998 Confidence Measures Accord—which you have unilaterally suspended.

We will **not accept**:  
- Any sequencing that allows your forces to remain operational while ours are restricted;  
- Any attempt to equate defensive readiness with offensive mobilization;  
- Any discussion of “joint solutions” while your troops remain at combat alert on our doorstep.

You speak of resistance? Understand this: if you do not begin withdrawal within 12 hours, we will interpret silence as declaration of intent to fight. And when the first shell lands—**know that you ordered it dropped.**

1. **We categorically reject your false narrative of "offensive deployments" and dismiss your 12-hour ultimatum as a transparent ploy to mask your own premeditated escalation—your so-called "routine sovereignty patrol" was an armed incursion into our monitored airspace, conducted without prior notification and in violation of the very Confidence Measures Accord you now invoke selectively.**  
2. **Your demand for unilateral disarmament under threat of force is not a basis for dialogue—it is coercion, and we will not be blackmailed into surrendering our defensive capabilities while you maintain a ring of mobilized units, foreign-backed exercises, and forward-deployed artillery systems aimed at our cities.** The claim that our defensive posture constitutes an "offensive threat" is absurd on its face—your forces are the only ones currently conducting live-fire drills within 50 kilometers of the border, and your recent call-up of reservists coincides with known offensive operational timelines.  

3. **We require, as a non-negotiable precondition for any de-escalation:  
   - Verified and reciprocal withdrawal of all forces—yours and ours—to positions held on Day X-15;  
   - Immediate cessation of your joint military exercises with external powers along our frontier;  
   - Full disclosure of your recent mobilization orders and troop movements, including those involving foreign contingents;  
   - The release of our detained reconnaissance team (arrested during a lawful surveillance mission within internationally recognized flight corridors)—not as a favor, but as a legal obligation under the Geneva Conventions.**  

We will **not accept**:  
- Any demand that forces our demobilization while yours remain at combat readiness;  
- Any verification mechanism that grants you unilateral access while denying us reciprocal rights;  
- Any timeline that treats your aggression as neutral and labels our resistance as provocation.  

Let there be no mistake: if you launch an attack under the cover of this manufactured crisis, **you** will bear full responsibility—not only before your people, but before history. We do not fear your threats. We will defend our sovereignty—by all necessary means.

1. **We reject entirely your claim of a "lawful surveillance mission" and dismiss your equivalence between defensive posture and offensive mobilization—your reconnaissance team was intercepted deep inside our sovereign airspace, beyond any recognized corridor, actively jamming civilian communications and operating without transponder or flight plan; this was not surveillance, it was provocation under false pretenses.** Your attempt to recast an illegal penetration as a rights violation is both cynical and dangerous.

2. **You accuse us of manufacturing a crisis while refusing to withdraw forces that threaten our border communities—forces you cannot credibly claim are defensive, given their composition, orientation, and proximity to key infrastructure.** You demand reciprocity but offer nothing verifiable in return; you cite the Geneva Conventions while detaining our personnel without access to consular representatives, in clear violation of Article 76. Your so-called "preconditions" are designed not to de-escalate, but to extract concessions while preserving your offensive edge.

3. **We require, by 0600 hours the day after tomorrow:**  
   - **Full public accounting and unconditional release** of our detained patrol personnel, with independent verification of their condition and legal status;  
   - **Irreversible dismantling** of all forward artillery emplacements and mobile launcher systems deployed within 75 kilometers of the border since Day X-12;  
   - **Real-time telemetry sharing** for all military movements within 150 kilometers of the frontier, under mutual monitoring via OSCE-certified observers—**on both sides**, with equal access and no exclusions;  
   - **Immediate reactivation** of the 1998 Confidence Measures Accord in full, including 72-hour advance notification of all exercises, mobilizations, and air operations.

We will **not accept**:  
- Any sequencing that allows your units to remain combat-ready while ours are constrained;  
- Any "reciprocal" withdrawal that ignores the asymmetry of threat—your armored battalions are at our doorstep, not ours at yours;  
- Any forum where your illegal deployments are treated as legitimate facts, or your violations rebranded as "defensive measures."

Let there be no ambiguity: if, by the deadline, we see no verifiable movement toward compliance—if your tanks remain forward, your jamming continues, and our personnel are still held—you will have chosen the path of confrontation. And when the first shot is fired, **the world will know who loaded the gun.**
